items.title: Awesome Robotic Tooling
items.content_text:
### Documentation and Presentation

*   [foam (‚≠ê16k)](https://github.com/foambubble/foam) - Foam is a personal knowledge management and sharing system inspired by Roam Research, built on Visual Studio Code and GitHub.

### Network and Middleware / Real-Time Kernel

*   [ros2arduino (‚≠ê236)](https://github.com/ROBOTIS-GIT/ros2arduino) - This library helps the Arduino board communicate with the ROS2 using XRCE-DDS.

### Network and Middleware / Ethernet and Wireless Networking

*   [airalab](https://github.com/airalab) -  AIRA is reference Robonomics network client for ROS-enabled cyber-physical systems.
*   [wireless (‚≠ê24)](https://github.com/clearpathrobotics/wireless) - Making info about wireless networks available to ROS.

### Network and Middleware / Controller Area Network

*   [opendbc (‚≠ê2.4k)](https://github.com/commaai/opendbc) - The project to democratize access to the decoder ring of your car.

### Network and Middleware / Sensor and Acuator Interfaces

*   [pacmod3 (‚≠ê27)](https://github.com/astuff/pacmod3) - This ROS node is designed to allow the user to control a vehicle with the PACMod drive-by-wire system, board revision 3.
*   [ros2\_intel\_realsense (‚≠ê145)](https://github.com/intel/ros2_intel_realsense) - These are packages for using Intel RealSense cameras (D400 series) with ROS2.
*   [sick\_scan (‚≠ê132)](https://github.com/SICKAG/sick_scan) - This stack provides a ROS2 driver for the SICK TiM series of laser scanners.
*   [ouster\_example (‚≠ê493)](https://github.com/ouster-lidar/ouster_example) - Sample code for connecting to and configuring the OS1, reading and visualizing data, and interfacing with ROS.
*   [sick\_safetyscanners (‚≠ê63)](https://github.com/SICKAG/sick_safetyscanners) - A ROS Driver which reads the raw data from the SICK Safety Scanners and publishes the data as a laser\_scan msg.
